_data.name: Freyam Mehta
_data.title: Software Engineer
_data.bio: I'm a pre-final year undergraduate at IIIT Hyderabad, majoring in Computer Science and Engineering. I have a demonstrated history of leading tech teams across multiple domains. I focus on delivering key outcomes and swiftly adjusting to new learnings to solve problems. I'm a natural at putting big ideas into action under pressure.
_data.description:
I'm a goal-driven husky who loves to use modern technologies to solve user problems. 
 I'm a firm believer in the potential of rural development schemes. I sleep well knowing that I'm doing my best to make the lives of the less fortunate better. To achieve this, I have been working with several Not-for-profit organizations and startups over the last two years. It's very fulfilling to work at startups as I can work closely with the founding team and grow with the company! 
 I'm an avid admirer of the open-source world. I have had the pleasure of contributing to and being part of some of the most incredible communities such as Dask, NumFOCUS, Google Cirq, Joomla!, OpenMRS, LibreHealth, RTEMS and CCExtractor. I'm grateful to Google Summer of Code for kindling my love for open-source, first as a student and then as a mentor! 
 In my free time, I watch lectures on Computer Networking and Finance Technology. I aspire to work professionally in these fields as I mature into my career. 
 I'm always looking forward to an insightful conversation over snacks or, even better, a game of cricket!

GirlScript Summer of Code is the three-month-long Open Source program during summers conducted by GirlScript Foundation, started in 2018, to help beginners get started with Open Source Development while encouraging diversity. Throughout the program, participants contribute to different projects under the guidance of experienced mentors.
tasks: Contributed to several projects built with Python and JavaScript.
Collaborated with like-minded students from across India on team projects.
Discussed breakthrough ideas with several open-source pioneers of the country.

_data.description: Specific workflows are required in Joomla! to complete certain activities. If users are new to the platform and wish to learn how to accomplish certain tasks, they must currently read the documentation. In Joomla!, this project should offer a guided tour feature. A tour is a click-through path that a user can take to complete specific tasks, such as writing an article.

_data.description: Dask's primary job is building task graphs and optimising them before decorating the functions to operate lazily.
tasks: Redeveloped the computational task graph visualisations by enhancing the visuals while being mentored by Genevieve Buckley (Scientist, Monash University) and Martin Durant (Senior Software and Data Engineer, Anaconda).
Expanded the visual output from 11% to 40% without compromising the performance factor.
Optimized the visualisations of existing dask collections to push extra metadata to the task graphs after discussions with partnering organisations such as NVIDIA.

_data.description: "Initiative on the Forest Economy" is an effort to create partnerships between local communities as custodians of forests, industries as the users and government as facilitators of wealth creation.

_data.description: Puhas is a farm-to-fork firm that evolved from a social enterprise to solve difficulties in the AgTech area and supply fresh fruit to merchants and customers. Puhas is part of a strategic alliance that has created two 'Kisan Pathshalas' (Farmer Schools) outside Ranchi, Jharkhand.

_data.name: Amigos App
_data.description: Amigos is a clever Friend Recommendation Application that inventively suggests friends to Users. The User Database is stored in an array of polished AVL (Adelson-Velsky and Landis) Trees. We are not just any other Social Media. Our remarkable CompatiFriend algorithm is using excellent computation to deliver accurate results.

_data.name: GIF Your Sorrows Away
_data.description: GYSA (GIF your sorrows away) is a browser extension that displays adorable GIFs of cute animals on your screen at random.

_data.name: GoodBoy - A Discord Bot
_data.description: A Discord bot that contextually reacts to the emotions depicted in the messages by using a RoBERTa-based NLP Model, a multi-class emotion analyzer, trained on 58 million tweets that analyses the messages in real time.

_data.name: Cat Image Classifier
_data.description: A Python Project implementing and training an L-layer Neural Network to classify cats vs non-cat images by using Logistic Regression and storing a cache to pass information from forward to back propagation (82.4% Accuracy).

_data.name: Paradise Hotel Manager
_data.description: A C++ Project implementing critical functions (add, search, sort, modify, display, delete, payment, check-in & check-out) that are required in a resort/hotel by using an optimised database of rooms and guests.

_data.name: Number Sign Classifier
_data.description: A Python Project implementing and training a Deep Neural Network in Tensorflow to classify number signs by using Logistic Regression and applying optimization methods such as (Stochastic) Gradient Descent, Momentum, RMSProp, and Adam (99.1% Accuracy).

_data.name: Pikachu Objectifier
_data.description: Pikachu Objectifier is a Deep Learning Classifier trained using YOLO (You Only Live Once) and the OpenCV framework for the fine-tuning of the dataset model. I shamelessly objectifiy Pikachus in this project.

_data.name: State Library Manager
_data.description: A C++ Project implementing critical functions (add, search, modify, display, delete, payment, issue & return) that are required in a library by using an optimised database of books and customers.

_data.name: Terrain Mapper and Rover Maneuver
_data.description: A cross-platform Unity AR mobile application that maps terrain in real time using a camera utility. It also hosts a real time free movement AR Rover which can be maneuvered by touch. Deep applications - Mars Rovers can be simulated using the 3D mapped terrains.
